OL,3,CMan walks 30 miles up and down pier in
OL,4,Cmemory of his wife
OL,6,F"I get such a buzz and sense of reward
OL,7,Ffor believing that I might be doing
OL,8,Fsomething good in helping somebody,
OL,9,Fcontributing to saving lives in a
OL,10,Fsmall way," he said.
OL,12,FMr Hobbs, who completed his first
OL,13,Fchallenge in 1994, said he has
OL,14,Freceived "tremendous support" over the
OL,15,Fyears.
OL,17,FHe said: "People have come back
OL,18,Fcontinually supporting me, and for
OL,19,Fevery single person who's helped me in
OL,20,Fthose thirty years, at any time, I'd
OL,21,Flike to say thank you."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/5
